Albert Lewis?

263
00:26:36,703 --> 00:26:41,299
Last time you saw me
I was 63, on a cardiac ward!

264
00:26:41,383 --> 00:26:44,295
You thought I was old
and decrepit, huh?

265
00:26:44,383 --> 00:26:47,056
Talking about "Ah, can't go on!"

266
00:26:47,143 --> 00:26:51,136
Who wants to be 63
throughout eternity?

267
00:26:51,223 --> 00:26:55,262
- Look at you on the water!
- Well, hello! Come on...

268
00:26:55,343 --> 00:26:58,221
walk along, feel the beat!

269
00:26:58,303 --> 00:27:01,295
Dancing on water!
Smooth as ever!

270
00:27:02,943 --> 00:27:05,411
And that was you...

271
00:27:05,503 --> 00:27:09,052
just now, when...when I died.

272
00:27:09,143 --> 00:27:13,261
I thought you recognised me,
because you called me "Doc".

273
00:27:13,343 --> 00:27:16,221
Me being your favourite doc.

274
00:27:16,303 --> 00:27:21,423
Could you lend me a hand? I'm
up to my ass in problems again.

275
00:27:21,503 --> 00:27:24,620
Oh, Chris...

276
00:27:25,823 --> 00:27:27,495
Come here.

277
00:27:27,583 --> 00:27:30,017
You are still kinda ugly.

278
00:27:31,623 --> 00:27:35,741
You taught me a lot, Chief.
Nice place you got here.

279
00:27:35,823 --> 00:27:38,383
No, no.
Nice place you got here.

280
00:27:38,463 --> 00:27:42,422
- Me?
- Sure, you're making all this.

281
00:27:42,503 --> 00:27:46,655
We're insecure at first,
so we need safety and comfort.

282
00:27:46,743 --> 00:27:50,577
We all paint our surroundings,
but you use real paint!

283
00:27:50,663 --> 00:27:54,212
There's so much here
she didn't paint.

284
00:27:55,343 --> 00:27:56,981
Like that bird.

285
00:27:58,703 --> 00:28:02,093
Annie gave you a start,
like holding onto handrails.

286
00:28:02,183 --> 00:28:03,935
You're creating a world.

287
00:28:04,023 --> 00:28:08,494
From your imagination,
from anything you want.

288
00:28:08,583 --> 00:28:12,576
- Why doesn't it move?
- It will when you want it to.

289
00:28:19,383 --> 00:28:21,339
Oh-hoh! You go, boy!

290
00:28:21,423 --> 00:28:24,256
- Can I make it dive?
- You're the painter!

291
00:28:24,343 --> 00:28:26,903
[Doc] It's your world!

292
00:28:29,543 --> 00:28:31,499
[Doc] Look at it go!

293
00:28:32,783 --> 00:28:36,093
- How about turquoise wings?
- Turquoise!

294
00:28:36,183 --> 00:28:39,414
[Chris]
And a little mauve, all right!

295
00:28:54,543 --> 00:28:57,774
- I didn't do that.
- No, I did.

296
00:28:57,863 --> 00:29:00,821
When we're together
it's like dual controls.

297
00:29:00,903 --> 00:29:05,419
- Can I make elephants fly?
- Didn't Annie paint a house?

298
00:29:10,463 --> 00:29:14,217
Yeah, it's our dream house.

299
00:29:15,783 --> 00:29:18,820
[Doc] Just a stroll
across the water.

300
00:29:18,903 --> 00:29:21,133
Let's take the shortcut.

301
00:29:25,183 --> 00:29:28,698
- Nice shortcut.
- It's easy, look at me!

302
00:29:28,783 --> 00:29:32,742
- I'm gonna drown.
- You're already dead.

303
00:29:32,823 --> 00:29:35,542
Am l...am I really here?

304
00:29:35,623 --> 00:29:40,492
What do you mean by "you"?
Your arm or your leg?

305
00:29:40,583 --> 00:29:42,653
- Partly.
- Really?

306
00:29:42,743 --> 00:29:46,452
- And if you lost your limbs?
- I'd still be me.

307
00:29:46,543 --> 00:29:50,138
- What is the "me"?
- My brain, I suppose.

308
00:29:50,223 --> 00:29:53,579
Your brain?
Your brain is a body part.

309
00:29:53,663 --> 00:29:57,656
Like your fingernail
or your heart. Why is that you?

310
00:29:57,743 --> 00:30:01,656
Because "I" am a voice
in my head.

311
00:30:01,743 --> 00:30:03,620
The part that thinks, feels.

312
00:30:03,703 --> 00:30:06,263
That is aware that I exist.

313
00:30:09,943 --> 00:30:15,779
[Doc] So if you're aware
you exist...then you do.

314
00:30:15,863 --> 00:30:17,979
That's why you're still here.

315
00:30:31,183 --> 00:30:35,461
[Doc] No windows. What aren't
you ready to see, I wonder?

316
00:30:37,863 --> 00:30:42,254
Drink it. Think it's
coffee and it will be.

317
00:30:42,343 --> 00:30:44,174
OK.

318
00:30:44,263 --> 00:30:46,823
It's coffee...

319
00:30:46,903 --> 00:30:48,973
Paint!

320
00:30:49,063 --> 00:30:50,416
Acrylic.

321
00:30:50,503 --> 00:30:54,382
- [Doc] Why is it so hard?
- What?

322
00:30:54,463 --> 00:30:57,739
Your brain is meat.
It rots and disappears.

323
00:30:57,823 --> 00:31:00,815
You thought that's all
there was to you?

324
00:31:02,903 --> 00:31:06,054
Like you're in your house now.

325
00:31:06,143 --> 00:31:09,374
You're IN your house,
you AREN'T your house.

326
00:31:09,463 --> 00:31:12,899
The house falls down,
you walk away.

327
00:31:12,983 --> 00:31:14,974
But I rebuilt, huh?

328
00:31:15,063 --> 00:31:17,623
You see your body
because you like seeing one.

329
00:31:17,703 --> 00:31:21,491
We're seeing
what we choose to see.

330
00:31:21,583 --> 00:31:23,938
Let me show you something.

331
00:31:46,823 --> 00:31:48,415
Ha!

332
00:31:55,183 --> 00:31:57,697
[Chris] It's real.
Where is the paint?

333
00:31:57,783 --> 00:32:02,334
[Doc] You don't need it any
more. This is your world now.

334
00:32:03,823 --> 00:32:06,257
Thought is real.

335
00:32:06,343 --> 00:32:11,701
Physical is the illusion.
Ironic, huh?

336
00:32:14,583 --> 00:32:18,053
- Where's God in all this?
- He's up there.

337
00:32:18,143 --> 00:32:22,022
Somewhere...
Shouting down that he loves us.

338
00:32:22,103 --> 00:32:25,300
Wondering why we can't hear him.
You think?

339
00:32:27,663 --> 00:32:30,700
Drink your coffee.

340
00:32:30,783 --> 00:32:34,014
- Needs milk.
- Don't push your luck.

341
00:32:47,405 --> 00:32:47,885
'What do you think, Christy?

342
00:32:47,885 --> 00:32:50,115
'What do you think, Christy?

343
00:32:51,845 --> 00:32:54,518
'Right here.

344
00:32:56,445 --> 00:32:59,039
'Like this? You think?

345
00:33:14,405 --> 00:33:17,795
'They say we live
in our minds anyway.

346
00:33:19,205 --> 00:33:24,279
'Having you with me,
like this, keeps me happy.

347
00:33:26,845 --> 00:33:29,917
'Why do I believe
you can hear me?

348
00:33:30,005 --> 00:33:33,077
'Why do I think
you can see this?'

349
00:33:38,125 --> 00:33:41,720
[Chris] What's that purple tree?
I never saw that.

350
00:33:41,805 --> 00:33:45,878
Let's look. Think you can
get there in eight seconds?

351
00:33:45,965 --> 00:33:49,514
Eight seconds? Over there?

352
00:33:49,605 --> 00:33:52,756
Yeah, I just need
a little incentive.

353
00:34:09,885 --> 00:34:14,083
Yeah... I can fly...

354
00:34:14,165 --> 00:34:16,474
- No!
- Can't I do what I want?

355
00:34:16,565 --> 00:34:20,558
I think you'd be more
comfortable keeping it real.

356
00:34:20,645 --> 00:34:23,955
Think of running fast,
like the Road Runner, OK?

357
00:34:30,405 --> 00:34:32,157
I can handle this.

358
00:34:35,125 --> 00:34:37,320
Adios, muchacho.

359
00:34:38,765 --> 00:34:40,756
Oh... Wait ! Chris !

360
00:34:40,845 --> 00:34:42,198
Annie!!

361
00:34:47,085 --> 00:34:49,804
I bet you're thinking
"Oh, shit!" now!

362
00:34:50,885 --> 00:34:53,035
Aaaaahhhh!

363
00:35:07,685 --> 00:35:10,074
- Yeah!
- Go, boy!

364
00:35:16,645 --> 00:35:18,078
Go, Chris, go!

365
00:35:43,325 --> 00:35:45,043
Albert!

366
00:35:45,125 --> 00:35:47,559
Albert!

367
00:35:54,405 --> 00:35:59,843
It's completely new. The canvas
was blank when I was alive.

368
00:36:01,245 --> 00:36:04,635
How can I see
this drawing after I'm dead?

369
00:36:04,725 --> 00:36:08,240
For an expert
you look pretty surprised.

370
00:36:08,325 --> 00:36:12,159
- You two. A long courtship?
- No, actually.

371
00:36:12,245 --> 00:36:15,601
- From the first moment...
- Soulmates.

372
00:36:15,685 --> 00:36:19,234
It's extremely rare,
but it exists.

373
00:36:19,325 --> 00:36:23,284
Like twin souls.
Tuned in to each other.

374
00:36:23,365 --> 00:36:26,118
Apparently, even in death.

375
00:36:27,605 --> 00:36:30,119
You're reaching each other
through her painting.

376
00:36:30,205 --> 00:36:33,595
It's nothing
I've ever seen.

377
00:36:34,965 --> 00:36:37,923
'You can't see it, can you?

378
00:36:40,365 --> 00:36:42,640
'And you never will.'

379
00:37:21,005 --> 00:37:22,882
I love you!

380
00:38:06,915 --> 00:38:09,713
[Chris]
Whose footprints are these?

381
00:38:09,795 --> 00:38:12,070
Don't ask,
you put 'em here.

382
00:38:24,435 --> 00:38:25,868
Annie...

383
00:38:25,955 --> 00:38:28,264
- Annie!
- [Doc] Chris!

384
00:38:36,195 --> 00:38:39,153
Fantasy is not what you need.

385
00:38:39,235 --> 00:38:43,194
No, you're right. I need Annie.

386
00:38:45,835 --> 00:38:49,464
- That'll change in time.
- Oh, come on, Einstein!

387
00:38:49,555 --> 00:38:54,424
Time's not on my watch any more!
Time does not exist here!

388
00:38:54,515 --> 00:38:58,224
Wherever it went, it won't
make me need Annie less.

389
00:39:00,235 --> 00:39:03,193
You'll feel differently,
and so will she.

390
00:39:03,275 --> 00:39:06,824
Man... You don't know us.

391
00:39:08,795 --> 00:39:10,353
Wish I did.

392
00:39:16,955 --> 00:39:18,468
[Chris] Marie...

393
00:39:18,555 --> 00:39:20,511
Marie!

394
00:39:25,475 --> 00:39:30,026
Look, it's Tigger!
It's my daughter's!

395
00:39:30,115 --> 00:39:32,993
Katie tore it up once, and...

396
00:39:36,715 --> 00:39:38,785
She's here, right?

397
00:39:38,875 --> 00:39:41,389
Where is she?

398
00:39:43,195 --> 00:39:46,949
"Here" is big enough
for all to have their universe.

399
00:39:49,315 --> 00:39:52,830
That's not why you
haven't seen them yet, is it?

400
00:39:54,235 --> 00:39:57,068
What does that mean, Buddha?

401
00:39:57,155 --> 00:39:59,874
I wanna see my children, Albert!

402
00:40:02,275 --> 00:40:05,153
When you do, you will.

403
00:40:20,915 --> 00:40:22,792
Does that hurt?

404
00:40:22,875 --> 00:40:24,024
Mm-mm.

405
00:40:24,115 --> 00:40:25,264
That?

406
00:40:25,355 --> 00:40:26,708
Mm-hm.

407
00:40:26,795 --> 00:40:28,672
How about that?

408
00:40:28,755 --> 00:40:32,031
I'm gonna keep doing this
till you tickle.

409
00:40:35,635 --> 00:40:38,786
You've got a fever.
It's going down, though.

410
00:40:38,875 --> 00:40:41,673
Don't you have to go somewhere?

411
00:40:43,115 --> 00:40:44,787
Wanna play chess?

412
00:40:48,115 --> 00:40:49,946
I could teach you.

413
00:40:50,035 --> 00:40:53,710
Would you teach me that?

414
00:41:20,915 --> 00:41:22,826
Excuse me.

415
00:41:25,155 --> 00:41:29,034
Albert has to work.
He asked me to meet with you.

416
00:41:29,115 --> 00:41:32,073
Will that be all right?

417
00:41:32,155 --> 00:41:35,352
Leona...
That's a very beautiful name.

418
00:41:35,435 --> 00:41:37,790
He said you've been isolated.

419
00:41:37,875 --> 00:41:42,312
Do you wanna see others?
Perhaps a city?

420
00:41:42,395 --> 00:41:45,307
I would,
but travel makes me nauseous.

421
00:41:51,675 --> 00:41:53,074
Close your eyes.

422
00:41:54,155 --> 00:41:57,465
I didn't mean forever.

423
00:42:08,235 --> 00:42:10,465
[Laughs] What do you think?

424
00:42:10,555 --> 00:42:12,785
I'm a little under-dressed.

425
00:42:12,875 --> 00:42:14,354
You look fine.

426
00:42:14,435 --> 00:42:18,587
Till now you've been painting
your world. This is mine.

427
00:42:18,675 --> 00:42:23,954
In our city across the river
we have to have a common vision.

428
00:42:37,635 --> 00:42:39,751
So, there's work.

429
00:42:39,835 --> 00:42:40,790
Mm-hm.

430
00:42:40,875 --> 00:42:42,308
I like that.

431
00:42:42,395 --> 00:42:46,149
Albert is sort of a missionary.

432
00:42:46,235 --> 00:42:49,432
- He saves lost souls.
- Like me.

433
00:42:49,515 --> 00:42:54,270
Hardly. They are the ones
who can't get here.

434
00:42:54,355 --> 00:42:56,073
You mean, from hell?

435
00:42:56,155 --> 00:42:59,352
In a way.
It's not what you think.

436
00:42:59,435 --> 00:43:02,791
My work is with animals.

437
00:43:04,035 --> 00:43:07,550
Katie is an old friend.

438
00:43:07,635 --> 00:43:09,034
'Dearest Christy.

439
00:43:09,115 --> 00:43:11,868
'l don't know how
this day unravelled.

440
00:43:11,955 --> 00:43:17,188
'l was proud of how I held
together through this afternoon.

441
00:43:17,275 --> 00:43:21,473
'But, coming home,
I began to lose it.

442
00:43:21,555 --> 00:43:24,228
'lf I had walked out that night,

443
00:43:24,315 --> 00:43:26,875
'you wouldn't have been
in the tunnel.

444
00:43:26,955 --> 00:43:31,824
'A whole family lost
in car crashes.

445
00:43:31,915 --> 00:43:33,906
'Enough to make a person
buy a bike.'

446
00:43:38,481 --> 00:43:40,312
[Chris] Where are they going?

447
00:43:40,401 --> 00:43:44,792
- To help others be reborn.
- Really? Reincarnation?

448
00:43:52,921 --> 00:43:55,754
Albert says to cheer you up.

449
00:43:55,841 --> 00:44:00,153
- You have difficulty...
- ..losing my wife, yeah.

450
00:44:00,241 --> 00:44:05,998
- And your children?
- They died years ago.

451
00:44:06,081 --> 00:44:08,754
That's why I'm worried
about my wife.

452
00:44:10,361 --> 00:44:12,591
They died
in a terrible collision.

453
00:44:12,681 --> 00:44:15,798
The nanny was driving.
It wasn't her fault.

454
00:44:15,881 --> 00:44:18,395
And your wife?

455
00:44:18,481 --> 00:44:22,156
My daughter
had asked her to drive.

456
00:44:22,241 --> 00:44:25,119
[Children's laughter]

457
00:44:37,801 --> 00:44:40,634
It was a trucker's fault.

458
00:44:40,721 --> 00:44:44,191
But my wife believed
that if she'd been driving,

459
00:44:44,281 --> 00:44:47,273
her protective instincts
would have...

460
00:44:59,201 --> 00:45:01,510
Are you OK?

461
00:45:07,681 --> 00:45:09,751
Come on, Katie!

462
00:45:22,601 --> 00:45:25,638
[Leona] Where were you just now?

463
00:45:25,721 --> 00:45:28,758
Your mind's been wandering
all afternoon.

464
00:45:28,841 --> 00:45:31,275
Thinking of someone.

465
00:45:32,761 --> 00:45:36,993
Your wife must have loved
her children very much.

466
00:45:37,081 --> 00:45:38,560
Very much.

467
00:45:38,641 --> 00:45:44,591
But you don't have to break
in half to love somebody.

468
00:45:44,681 --> 00:45:48,469
Tell me a memory of your own.

469
00:45:48,561 --> 00:45:51,200
Say, with your daughter.

470
00:46:08,481 --> 00:46:12,997
Hey...
That's somebody else's art.

471
00:46:13,081 --> 00:46:16,198
What's the difference?
You weren't looking anyway.

472
00:46:20,401 --> 00:46:22,119
Your move.

473
00:46:24,161 --> 00:46:27,471
Is this where we go when we die?

474
00:46:32,241 --> 00:46:35,517
It's a dream, baby.
It's beautiful,

475
00:46:35,601 --> 00:46:39,879
- but you know, dreams...
- ..l know, aren't real.

476
00:46:44,321 --> 00:46:47,119
- It's after midnight.
- I haven't won yet.

477
00:46:47,201 --> 00:46:49,795
- It's your first time.
- No, I like that.

478
00:46:49,881 --> 00:46:55,478
Means you're not cheating.
And when I win, I really win.

479
00:46:55,561 --> 00:46:57,791
I wanna play till I do.

480
00:46:57,881 --> 00:47:01,556
- Unless you wanna stop.
- No. Let's play till you win.

481
00:47:04,561 --> 00:47:07,598
'She died three months later.'

482
00:47:07,681 --> 00:47:10,593
We played every night.

483
00:47:12,401 --> 00:47:14,961
It meant the world to me.

484
00:47:16,281 --> 00:47:18,556
She never won.

485
00:47:44,521 --> 00:47:48,275
I didn't look like this
in the body, you know.

486
00:47:50,801 --> 00:47:53,759
We flew to Singapore once.
And...

487
00:47:53,841 --> 00:47:57,993
..my daddy smiled at
the flight attendant who...

488
00:48:00,161 --> 00:48:03,278
Iooked like this
and wore this name tag.

489
00:48:06,801 --> 00:48:09,474
He said Asian women are so...

490
00:48:10,681 --> 00:48:15,118
Iovely...and graceful...

491
00:48:15,201 --> 00:48:18,557
- and intelligent.
- He didn't mean only.

492
00:48:18,641 --> 00:48:20,871
I know.
It was something he said.

493
00:48:20,961 --> 00:48:25,591
And I thought, when I grow up,
I wanna be that.

494
00:48:27,801 --> 00:48:30,474
You still play chess?

495
00:48:38,881 --> 00:48:42,112
I think I waited for my partner.

496
00:49:22,519 --> 00:49:26,717
'l swear that California
is the strangest place.

497
00:49:26,799 --> 00:49:28,630
'They push you into it

498
00:49:28,719 --> 00:49:32,428
'so you can do it before
your shrink commits you.

499
00:49:32,519 --> 00:49:35,716
'Thoughtful legislation there.

500
00:49:35,799 --> 00:49:38,154
'Mine is suspicious.

501
00:49:38,239 --> 00:49:40,309
'Another week,
he might commit me.

502
00:49:40,399 --> 00:49:42,276
'For my own safety.

503
00:49:44,639 --> 00:49:47,995
'l had the husband
I was meant to have.

504
00:49:48,079 --> 00:49:50,639
'Two spectacular children.

505
00:49:50,719 --> 00:49:54,632
'Blessings no one would
dare expect from life.

506
00:49:56,159 --> 00:49:58,548
'And the truth is, simply...

507
00:50:00,319 --> 00:50:03,072
'that it's over.

508
00:50:03,159 --> 00:50:07,198
'Just this one loose end
to ravel up.

509
00:50:12,159 --> 00:50:16,710
'l didn't get to say goodbye.
You're dead and I blew that.

510
00:50:18,279 --> 00:50:21,555
'l don't get to say goodbye.

511
00:50:23,599 --> 00:50:25,908
'But I'll tell you what -

512
00:50:25,999 --> 00:50:29,196
'across whatever
distance there is,

513
00:50:31,319 --> 00:50:33,674
'l send you my love.'

514
00:50:46,479 --> 00:50:48,390
Hey.

515
00:50:50,519 --> 00:50:53,033
- Where were you?
- Far away.

516
00:50:53,119 --> 00:50:57,749
I got called back.
I was working.

517
00:50:57,839 --> 00:51:00,717
There are no words
to thank you.

518
00:51:00,799 --> 00:51:02,755
For finding Marie.

519
00:51:04,079 --> 00:51:05,797
[Sighs]

520
00:51:05,879 --> 00:51:07,995
- Is she OK?
- She's fine.

521
00:51:08,079 --> 00:51:10,434
You'll see her soon.

522
00:51:10,519 --> 00:51:14,797
She sends her love.
Especially now.

523
00:51:21,879 --> 00:51:26,350
We'll go through
something very hard right now.

524
00:51:26,439 --> 00:51:29,112
I'm with you. You're not alone.

525
00:51:31,479 --> 00:51:33,435
Annie is dead.

526
00:51:37,199 --> 00:51:39,554
She killed herself.

527
00:51:45,079 --> 00:51:47,513
It's nothing I ever expected.

528
00:51:49,359 --> 00:51:52,157
Like I said, you don't know us.

529
00:51:54,359 --> 00:51:57,396
Is that an occupational hazard
of soulmates?

530
00:51:57,479 --> 00:52:00,073
One's not much
without the other?

531
00:52:02,639 --> 00:52:04,914
But she's OK.

532
00:52:04,999 --> 00:52:07,593
Because her pain is over.

533
00:52:07,679 --> 00:52:10,512
- You don't understand.
- She won't cling like me.

534
00:52:10,599 --> 00:52:13,557
- When do I see her?
- Never.

535
00:52:16,279 --> 00:52:20,113
You'll never see her.
Suicides go somewhere else.

536
00:52:20,199 --> 00:52:23,874
- Why are you punishing her?
- It's not punishment.

537
00:52:23,959 --> 00:52:27,315
- She's suffered enough.
- There are no judges or crimes.

538
00:52:27,399 --> 00:52:30,038
Everybody's equal.
