01:14:40,819 --> 01:14:45,813
It's just that when everybody's
dancing I feel like I'm alone...

769
01:14:45,899 --> 01:14:48,618
..in a sea of faces.

770
01:14:51,179 --> 01:14:55,809
[Silent]

771
01:14:58,299 --> 01:14:59,652
Ahhh!

772
01:15:33,339 --> 01:15:36,012
Angel Falls...

773
01:15:36,099 --> 01:15:38,294
[Whistles]

774
01:15:38,379 --> 01:15:40,847
It's a little expensive, yeah.

775
01:15:40,939 --> 01:15:45,694
But it's our first Double D.
Shouldn't it be incredible?

776
01:15:48,059 --> 01:15:51,938
I've never seen
anything like it.

777
01:15:52,019 --> 01:15:56,171
That's my role.
To bring adventure to your life.

778
01:16:00,179 --> 01:16:03,251
You...taught me...

779
01:16:03,339 --> 01:16:07,617
the only thing
I should always remember.

780
01:16:07,699 --> 01:16:10,054
Which is?

781
01:16:12,139 --> 01:16:14,334
I forgot.

782
01:16:19,499 --> 01:16:22,252
Oh yeah, oh yeah, oh yeah...

783
01:16:23,619 --> 01:16:25,769
It was, never give up.

784
01:16:28,339 --> 01:16:30,853
Never give up.

785
01:16:33,659 --> 01:16:35,775
Never.

786
01:16:42,859 --> 01:16:44,975
[Tracker] She's here.

787
01:16:46,899 --> 01:16:51,097
You found her.
Impressive.

788
01:16:51,179 --> 01:16:54,091
That jolt of fear for her.
It connected.

789
01:16:54,179 --> 01:16:57,649
[Chris]
My God, is that our house?

790
01:17:17,139 --> 01:17:19,573
- It's like our home.
- Don't think that.

791
01:17:19,659 --> 01:17:23,208
[Tracker] It's an illusion.

792
01:17:23,299 --> 01:17:26,575
The whole place...her illusion.

793
01:17:26,659 --> 01:17:28,536
Suicides can get tortured,

794
01:17:28,619 --> 01:17:30,769
committed to
punishing themselves.

795
01:17:30,859 --> 01:17:32,770
Don't push her that way.

796
01:17:32,859 --> 01:17:34,611
You want to see her.

797
01:17:34,699 --> 01:17:37,896
Tell her what's in your heart.
And then go.

798
01:17:39,379 --> 01:17:41,335
- No pressure.
- Wait!

799
01:17:42,739 --> 01:17:46,049
I knew you'd find her.
You're a competitor.

800
01:17:46,139 --> 01:17:49,575
How d'you know
the first thing about me?

801
01:17:49,659 --> 01:17:53,368
You called your son Albert.
Who is that?

802
01:17:53,459 --> 01:17:56,690
First doctor I interned under.

803
01:17:58,179 --> 01:18:00,613
He was like a father to me.

804
01:18:00,699 --> 01:18:03,259
His words were gold.
A brilliant mind.

805
01:18:03,339 --> 01:18:06,490
What did he practice
before turning to pediatrics?

806
01:18:09,259 --> 01:18:12,968
- Child psychia...
- ..psychiatry.

807
01:18:13,059 --> 01:18:16,449
And he was always...
a slow reader.

808
01:18:17,699 --> 01:18:22,215
But these...used to be rimless.

809
01:18:22,299 --> 01:18:27,692
And the rest of me...
used to be black.

810
01:18:37,979 --> 01:18:41,733
You know why we chose to look
different? Me, the children?

811
01:18:41,819 --> 01:18:44,652
Package doesn't count?
One's as good as...

812
01:18:44,739 --> 01:18:47,572
No. The old roles of authority.

813
01:18:47,659 --> 01:18:50,048
Who's the teacher,
who's the father...

814
01:18:50,139 --> 01:18:55,452
gets in the way of who
we really are...to each other.

815
01:18:55,539 --> 01:19:00,374
I've waited for years for
a chance to watch out for you.

816
01:19:00,459 --> 01:19:03,974
And I'm watching
out for you now.

817
01:19:04,059 --> 01:19:06,527
But this isn't like
the rest of hell.

818
01:19:06,619 --> 01:19:10,612
You've got no defence
against Annie.

819
01:19:10,699 --> 01:19:14,977
If losing yourself or
being swallowed by hell itself

820
01:19:15,059 --> 01:19:19,416
could save her,
I'd be there cheering you on.

821
01:19:20,779 --> 01:19:23,771
You've got
your children back now.

822
01:19:23,859 --> 01:19:25,690
They need you.

823
01:19:25,779 --> 01:19:30,569
Three minutes... Any more,
you could lose your mind.

824
01:19:30,659 --> 01:19:32,934
[Chris]
How can you lose your mind?

825
01:19:33,019 --> 01:19:35,089
[Tracker]
Once her reality becomes yours,

826
01:19:35,179 --> 01:19:38,694
there's really no way back.

827
01:19:54,109 --> 01:19:56,065
[Ian] 'Think about Mom.'

828
01:19:57,669 --> 01:20:00,547
'What you said
to bring her back.'

829
01:20:12,229 --> 01:20:15,619
Hello?
Your door's open. [Echoes]

830
01:20:48,909 --> 01:20:52,379
Sorry,
I didn't mean to scare you.

831
01:20:54,669 --> 01:20:59,379
- Who...who are you?
- I'm your neighbour.

832
01:20:59,469 --> 01:21:02,666
I bought the Gorman's place
two months ago.

833
01:21:02,749 --> 01:21:04,626
I just moved in.

834
01:21:04,709 --> 01:21:08,145
I never heard
they sold their place.

835
01:21:08,229 --> 01:21:12,541
You're Annie Nielsen, right?

836
01:21:12,629 --> 01:21:15,143
They told me a lot about you.

837
01:21:15,229 --> 01:21:17,424
Like what? What did they say?

838
01:21:17,509 --> 01:21:20,467
That you're
a very talented artist and...

839
01:21:20,549 --> 01:21:23,507
work for a museum, right? And...

840
01:21:23,589 --> 01:21:25,227
you're a widow.

841
01:21:26,349 --> 01:21:28,624
Mrs Gorman admires your roses...

842
01:21:28,709 --> 01:21:32,224
very much.

843
01:21:32,309 --> 01:21:35,301
They were so handsome.

844
01:21:36,909 --> 01:21:40,299
But now there's no water
pressure in the neighbourhood.

845
01:21:40,389 --> 01:21:46,021
There's no electricity
and no gas.

846
01:21:46,109 --> 01:21:49,226
There are other things
missing, too.

847
01:21:49,309 --> 01:21:52,699
Like clean clothes
and books I want to read.

848
01:21:52,789 --> 01:21:54,108
And, um...

849
01:21:54,189 --> 01:21:58,899
some of my favourite
paintings I have to work on.

850
01:22:02,029 --> 01:22:03,587
Aahh!

851
01:22:04,869 --> 01:22:08,384
- What is it?
- They're everywhere now!

852
01:22:10,189 --> 01:22:12,145
I got it!

853
01:22:14,229 --> 01:22:15,787
It's gone.

854
01:22:22,229 --> 01:22:23,628
Thank you.

855
01:22:26,149 --> 01:22:27,946
You're welcome.

856
01:22:28,029 --> 01:22:30,304
You say your paintings
are missing.

857
01:22:30,389 --> 01:22:33,904
Some of my most precious panels.

858
01:22:33,989 --> 01:22:35,866
The ones that remind me.

859
01:22:43,429 --> 01:22:46,546
Remind me of my husband
and my children.

860
01:22:46,629 --> 01:22:50,542
That's why I never leave.

861
01:22:50,629 --> 01:22:53,507
Because they might return?

862
01:22:55,989 --> 01:22:58,708
I hope that's true
with all my heart.

863
01:22:58,789 --> 01:23:01,223
It's not, you know.

864
01:23:01,309 --> 01:23:05,825
When you're dead, you disappear.

865
01:23:07,709 --> 01:23:12,305
My wife committed suicide
after our children died.

866
01:23:12,389 --> 01:23:14,425
After l...

867
01:23:14,509 --> 01:23:18,422
She was the loveliest person.

868
01:23:18,509 --> 01:23:20,386
Don't you think that's sad?

869
01:23:20,469 --> 01:23:23,620
- Don't you have to leave?
- No.

870
01:23:23,709 --> 01:23:27,907
- But if you want me to go...
- I do.

871
01:23:27,989 --> 01:23:31,823
The last day I saw my wife
it was our anniversary.

872
01:23:31,909 --> 01:23:34,139
- Aren't you leaving?
- In a minute.

873
01:23:34,229 --> 01:23:37,983
I was sticking around in case
there was another problem.

874
01:23:38,069 --> 01:23:40,219
It wasn't a wedding anniversary.

875
01:23:40,309 --> 01:23:43,824
It was a very
special kind of day...

876
01:23:45,389 --> 01:23:48,904
..no one else knows about.

877
01:23:57,909 --> 01:23:59,945
[Annie humming]

878
01:24:02,869 --> 01:24:05,463
[Chris] I need to talk to you.

879
01:24:05,549 --> 01:24:08,382
And you don't have to respond.

880
01:24:14,909 --> 01:24:19,346
This is a one-way ticket...
for me.

881
01:24:21,189 --> 01:24:24,101
My hanging around here
is not helping you.

882
01:24:24,189 --> 01:24:26,305
And it's killing me.

883
01:24:26,389 --> 01:24:29,301
Today is kind of a D-Day.

884
01:24:30,629 --> 01:24:33,939
"D" for decision, I guess.

885
01:24:36,549 --> 01:24:38,699
About divorce.

886
01:24:39,989 --> 01:24:42,378
That'd be two D's,
wouldn't it?

887
01:24:47,789 --> 01:24:50,098
I stand corrected.

888
01:24:55,069 --> 01:24:59,142
Look what happens when you
don't say anything for a month.

889
01:25:00,709 --> 01:25:02,700
Cindy called.

890
01:25:02,789 --> 01:25:05,257
She said
everything is waiting for you.

891
01:25:07,189 --> 01:25:12,343
The artists and curators will
see you when you're better.

892
01:25:12,429 --> 01:25:15,307
And I told her...

893
01:25:15,389 --> 01:25:20,258
it was the museum
and one of those meetings

894
01:25:20,349 --> 01:25:23,147
that kept you
from driving that day.

895
01:25:25,949 --> 01:25:29,988
And if you went back,
it'd mean you weren't sorry,

896
01:25:30,069 --> 01:25:34,620
you weren't wrong and you'd
be betraying your children.

897
01:25:34,709 --> 01:25:38,258
She called you crazy
and I called her a bitch!

898
01:25:38,349 --> 01:25:42,467
And I hung up!
That didn't go very well!

899
01:25:46,629 --> 01:25:49,701
What's true in our minds
is true.

900
01:25:49,789 --> 01:25:53,020
Whether some people
know it or not.

901
01:25:54,509 --> 01:25:58,582
That's when I realised
I'm part of the problem.

902
01:25:58,669 --> 01:26:02,298
Not because I remind you.

903
01:26:02,389 --> 01:26:05,699
But because I couldn't join you.

904
01:26:05,789 --> 01:26:09,225
So I left you alone.

905
01:26:14,909 --> 01:26:16,740
Don't give up, OK?

906
01:26:29,349 --> 01:26:30,828
OK.

907
01:26:32,069 --> 01:26:33,946
OK.

908
01:26:35,029 --> 01:26:36,906
It's OK.

909
01:26:53,629 --> 01:26:55,426
[Annie] So you reconciled.

910
01:26:58,229 --> 01:27:00,618
That's very romantic.

911
01:27:01,829 --> 01:27:03,979
She still killed herself.

912
01:27:05,989 --> 01:27:08,901
- She gave up.
- There's nothing wrong with it.

913
01:27:08,989 --> 01:27:11,457
- Her husband thought so.
- He was a coward!

914
01:27:11,549 --> 01:27:15,178
Being strong, not giving up...

915
01:27:15,269 --> 01:27:17,737
that was his place to hide.

916
01:27:17,829 --> 01:27:20,707
He pushed away the pain so hard,

917
01:27:20,789 --> 01:27:24,907
he disconnected himself from
the person he loved the most.

918
01:27:27,149 --> 01:27:30,983
Sometimes,
when you win, you lose.

919
01:27:37,869 --> 01:27:39,939
When he saw
his children again...

920
01:27:40,029 --> 01:27:42,338
I thought
your children were dead.

921
01:27:43,789 --> 01:27:46,906
You can see the dead.
In your dreams.

922
01:27:46,989 --> 01:27:49,742
If you want to.

923
01:27:52,469 --> 01:27:55,302
I wanna see Christy.

924
01:27:56,749 --> 01:27:59,343
I can show you.
It's not hard.

925
01:27:59,429 --> 01:28:03,183
All you have to do...
it's like painting a picture.

926
01:28:03,269 --> 01:28:05,419
We do it together.

927
01:28:05,509 --> 01:28:09,582
Just close your eyes. (Please.)

928
01:28:09,669 --> 01:28:12,342
(Don't be afraid.)

929
01:28:14,549 --> 01:28:17,302
Remember where you were married?

930
01:28:23,389 --> 01:28:25,584
Christy!

931
01:28:25,669 --> 01:28:27,148
Christy...

932
01:28:28,549 --> 01:28:32,462
Who else would you
be marrying in your dreams?

933
01:28:34,309 --> 01:28:36,743
[Annie] I missed you.

934
01:28:37,829 --> 01:28:39,626
Annie...

935
01:28:39,709 --> 01:28:42,348
This is real.

936
01:28:45,269 --> 01:28:47,385
The man in the garden.

937
01:28:50,869 --> 01:28:53,064
It's me.

938
01:28:55,829 --> 01:28:57,421
No!

939
01:28:57,509 --> 01:28:58,908
No!

940
01:29:00,669 --> 01:29:02,341
Whoever you are,

941
01:29:02,429 --> 01:29:06,468
did you think
you could take him from me?

942
01:29:19,069 --> 01:29:21,185
I'm sorry, babe.

943
01:29:21,269 --> 01:29:23,829
There's some things
I have to say.

944
01:29:23,909 --> 01:29:27,379
I've only got
a few moments left.

945
01:29:29,029 --> 01:29:32,863
I'm sorry for all the things
I'll never give you.

946
01:29:32,949 --> 01:29:36,988
I'll never buy you another
meatball sub with extra sauce.

947
01:29:37,069 --> 01:29:40,266
And always the big one.

948
01:29:40,349 --> 01:29:42,863
I'll never make you smile.

949
01:29:45,229 --> 01:29:48,027
I just wanted us
to be old together.

950
01:29:48,109 --> 01:29:53,263
Two old farts laughing at each
other as our bodies fell apart.

951
01:29:53,349 --> 01:29:55,260
Together at the end.

952
01:29:55,349 --> 01:29:58,466
By that lake in your painting.

953
01:29:58,549 --> 01:30:01,507
That was our heaven, see?

954
01:30:01,589 --> 01:30:04,149
There's lots of things to miss.

955
01:30:05,589 --> 01:30:08,706
Books...naps...

956
01:30:08,789 --> 01:30:12,543
kisses...and fights.

957
01:30:12,629 --> 01:30:16,304
Oh, God, we had
some great ones!

958
01:30:16,389 --> 01:30:18,949
(Thank you for those.)

959
01:30:20,469 --> 01:30:23,188
Thank you for every kindness.

960
01:30:24,709 --> 01:30:27,098
Thank you for our children.

961
01:30:27,189 --> 01:30:29,828
For the first time I saw them.

962
01:30:31,469 --> 01:30:36,145
Thank you for being someone
I was always proud to be with.

963
01:30:37,909 --> 01:30:39,979
For your guts,

964
01:30:40,069 --> 01:30:41,468
for your sweetness.

965
01:30:41,549 --> 01:30:43,779
For how you always looked,

966
01:30:43,869 --> 01:30:46,781
for how I always wanted
to touch you.

967
01:30:48,269 --> 01:30:51,227
God, you were my life.

968
01:30:53,069 --> 01:30:57,062
I apologise for every time
I failed you.

969
01:30:57,149 --> 01:30:59,788
Especially this one.

970
01:31:20,823 --> 01:31:25,260
- Didn't you think I'd make it?
- You were in there a while.

971
01:31:25,343 --> 01:31:29,131
Took me a while to realise
you were right.

972
01:31:29,223 --> 01:31:32,454
Nothing you can do
could help her.

973
01:31:32,543 --> 01:31:34,613
This trip was for you.

974
01:31:36,903 --> 01:31:39,815
- Did you come close...
- ..to losing it?

975
01:31:39,903 --> 01:31:41,859
Oh, yeah.

976
01:31:41,943 --> 01:31:45,060
Pushed it right to the edge.

977
01:31:45,143 --> 01:31:48,294
That's why
I had to come out now.

978
01:31:48,383 --> 01:31:50,578
I'm giving up.

979
01:31:53,023 --> 01:31:54,934
Not the way you think.

980
01:31:59,023 --> 01:32:00,536
Go home, Al.

981
01:32:01,823 --> 01:32:05,179
Will you tell my children
I love them?

982
01:32:06,343 --> 01:32:08,777
And I won't leave their mother.

983
01:32:12,983 --> 01:32:14,894
(Thanks.)

984
01:32:21,023 --> 01:32:22,695
Where are we headed?

985
01:32:24,983 --> 01:32:30,455
In one minute I won't know you
any better than you'll know me.

986
01:32:30,543 --> 01:32:34,092
But we'll be together.

987
01:32:34,183 --> 01:32:36,299
Where we belong.

988
01:32:38,103 --> 01:32:42,494
Good people go to hell because
they can't forgive themselves.

989
01:32:42,583 --> 01:32:44,653
I know I can't.

990
01:32:44,743 --> 01:32:47,541
But I can forgive you.

991
01:32:47,623 --> 01:32:50,820
For killing my children?

992
01:32:51,983 --> 01:32:54,577
And my sweet husband?

993
01:32:54,663 --> 01:32:56,972
(No.)

994
01:32:57,063 --> 01:33:01,102
For being so wonderful, a guy
would choose hell over heaven,

995
01:33:01,183 --> 01:33:03,697
just to hang around you.

996
01:33:08,143 --> 01:33:10,896
Not because I remind you...

997
01:33:10,983 --> 01:33:13,941
but because I couldn't join you.

998
01:33:14,023 --> 01:33:17,413
Sorry I left you alone.

999
01:33:19,183 --> 01:33:22,095
Don't give up, OK?

1000
01:33:39,983 --> 01:33:42,451
Christy?

1001
01:33:46,903 --> 01:33:49,212
Christy.

1002
01:33:52,423 --> 01:33:54,334
What happened to this place?

1003
01:33:57,823 --> 01:34:00,735
It's cold.

1004
01:34:12,623 --> 01:34:14,500
Christy?

1005
01:34:14,583 --> 01:34:17,541
God, no! No, no, no, no!

1006
01:34:17,623 --> 01:34:20,091
Don't give up!
Don't give up! Christy!

1007
01:34:20,183 --> 01:34:23,380
Don't give up!
Don't, don't give up!

1008
01:34:23,463 --> 01:34:25,215
Christy!

1009
01:34:28,383 --> 01:34:30,817
[Fading] Stay with me,
don't give up...

1010
01:34:51,223 --> 01:34:52,053
[Annie] Christy!

1011
01:35:28,221 --> 01:35:29,700
Hey!

1012
01:35:31,821 --> 01:35:33,891
Remember me?

1013
01:35:43,621 --> 01:35:46,579
Sometimes, when you lose...

1014
01:35:46,661 --> 01:35:48,174
you win.

1015
01:36:40,701 --> 01:36:42,692
How did we get here?

1016
01:36:46,301 --> 01:36:49,930
Travel here
is like everything else.

1017
01:36:50,021 --> 01:36:52,296
It's in your mind.

1018
01:36:53,541 --> 01:36:56,374
You only have to
close your eyes.

1019
01:36:56,461 --> 01:36:59,931
If you know
where you're going...

1020
01:37:00,021 --> 01:37:03,297
Looks like we did.

1021
01:37:04,781 --> 01:37:06,612
Where you were...

1022
01:37:08,301 --> 01:37:11,179
I tried everything.
Nothing worked.

1023
01:37:12,941 --> 01:37:14,932
Until...

1024
01:37:15,021 --> 01:37:17,615
you tried trailing me.

1025
01:37:22,181 --> 01:37:25,935
What some folks
call impossible...

1026
01:37:26,021 --> 01:37:29,377
is what
they haven't seen before.

1027
01:38:08,621 --> 01:38:10,054
Excuse me, lady.

